Road.Name: 19 Prebend Street
Other.Comments: Crooks who try to take advantage of students and their lack of experience living away from home.

Road.Name: Welford Road
Other.Comments: House is great, but the Clarendon Park area is prone to burglaries so be sure not to leave any valuables over the holiday periods!

Road.Name: Prebend Street
Other.Comments: Difficult to contact, very unreliable. House was in a state when we moved in, yet when we moved out they took all of our deposits 'to clean it for the next tenants'. Awful estate agents!

Road.Name: Devonshire Road
Other.Comments: Hastings itself is a very lovely town filled with amazing people. Everyone is an individual, it's like a small slice of Brighton and London combined. However it hasn't got any clubs. So for me it's a great area, quiet and relaxed. For most students it's deemed boring. It has the largest underground skatepark in Europe added in early 2016 which is amazing and the pier has just reopened, so Hastings is on the up!

Road.Name: Rupert Street
Other.Comments: Good location - 20 minute walk to the university, easy walk into the city centre and round the corner from a subway station. Various buses also run from end of road.  Near Lidl and other smaller supermarkets, bars and restaurants. Some noise from busy Great Western Road.

Road.Name: Prebend Street
Other.Comments: Shit

Road.Name: Hamilton Street
Other.Comments: Evington is a rough place to live in Leicester but you get bigger houses so better if a big group of you want to live together! Make sure you live on the outskirts of evington as it's pretty scary in the evenings!

Road.Name: University Road, David Collet
Other.Comments: Warden was very helpful and a good problems solver. Accommodation overall was average but needed a refurb

Road.Name: Brookland Road
Other.Comments: Although it looks great, it is very expensive for somewhere that has very thin walls and rubbish appliances. Sulets as an agent were unhelpful and disregarding of issues caused by other students. Great if you are 2nd year and aren't worried about final assignments- not good for those who need sleep!

Road.Name: Amherst Road
Other.Comments: Recent graduate. All the above is based on memory. However Navid generally proved to be incredibly polite and was genuinely a lovely landlord. The only issues were the inconsistency in fixing things that were broken. For instance our TV channels stopped working due to the ariel which was attached round the back of the house leading to the roof being broken. After a few attempts Navid seemingly gave up and didn't bother fixing it. This wouldn't have been a huge issue considering we used Netflix via the PS3 over the TV channels. What was frustrating however is that he said he would get us a TV if we bought a TV license which we did, yet it wasn't worth it considering he didn't fix the ariel issue.

Road.Name: Highfield Street
Other.Comments: The house was okay and quite liveable. The area has a bad reputation but really isn't that bad given its proximity to uni. The big issue was Jalaram - they did not address any issues sufficiently, were patronising and extremely rude at times.

Road.Name: Bulwer Road
Other.Comments: Landlords are quick to respond but a bit over-present. The house is very nice but I wouldn't say it was suitable for 3 people if you are planning on cooking separately. If you are all eating together it would be fine. Bathroom needs better ventilation - a bit prone to mould.

Road.Name: Salisbury Road
Other.Comments: Brilliant landlord. Went out of his way to help us even when the estate agents wouldn't.

Road.Name: Shirley Road
Other.Comments: Took them weeks to solve problems. Rude and tried to scam us out of our deposit.

Road.Name: Clarendon Park Road
Other.Comments: Landlord is great. Unfortunately Sulets are unreliable - lack of communication between staff. Many of the things we contacted them about were either not noted down or not of their concern. Frequently had to contact landlord directly - landlords were brilliant and always quick to resolve issues.

Road.Name: Glanmor Crescent
Other.Comments: Don't seem to care about problems, so we had to sort them all out ourselves

Road.Name: Welford Road
Other.Comments: Avoid at all costs. The worst agency I have ever dealt with. Take forever to respond ever after being constantly pestered.

Road.Name: Adderley Road
Other.Comments: Would not recommend Priya at all. They are very bad at communicating with regards to bills (we weren't told who our energy supplier was) and any problems we had were dealt with very slowly, if at all.

Road.Name: Adderley Road
Other.Comments: Would not recommend Priya at all. They are very bad at communicating with regards to bills (we weren't told who our energy supplier was) and any problems we had were dealt with very slowly, if at all.

Road.Name: Welford road
Other.Comments: Habitio were absolutely terrible

Road.Name: Leopold street
Other.Comments: We were really lucky with our letting agents, they got back to you really quickly if you had a problem and the house was in really good condition.

Road.Name: 15 Oxford Road
Other.Comments: When we first arrived in the house the toliet was broken, the bathtub, and the fridge leaked alot. Single glazed windows were a bitch in the winter too.

Road.Name: 43 St Leonard's Road
Other.Comments: The oven door broke. The oven did still work but it never got fully fixed which effected our food. Also there was a leak from the bath to the kitchen which never got properly solved. Overall everything was still in ok working order, rooms are big and walk to uni is about 5mins

Road.Name: Ladybarn Road
Other.Comments: Great location but the house is slightly on the smaller side for 5 people. Landlord was pleasant and organised. BILLS INCLUDED for the price which is amazing - comes with everything set up, Sky TV, internet etc.

Road.Name: Lombard Grove
Other.Comments: Great 9 bedroom house in a fantastic location

Road.Name: Dunluce
Other.Comments: Good if your at the top near lisburn road, further down can get funny.

Road.Name: Putney Road
Other.Comments: I don't live in a rented apartment or house actually,I live in 'university accommodation', so the questions on deposit and landlord-relationships weren't quite meaningful in my case.

Road.Name: Hamilton Street
Other.Comments: Will fix things but will always send Adam which is good. Joy is a nightmare! Doesn't know how to cumminicate politely so always come across very rude and will always argue if you try and constructively criticise anything or complain about something you don't like her doing

Road.Name: Welford road
Other.Comments: The house is lovely and an old style. Kitchen looks old and I know there are more modern houses but if anything broke he bought us a replacement brand new! Washing machine broke one day and the next day we had a brand new Samsung bubble machine delivered. An absolutely incredible and polite landlord who really will go out of his way to make sure you enjoy staying there.

Road.Name: Canterbury Court, Kent Road East
Address: Canterbury Court, Kent Road East, M14 5BX

Road.Name: 24 Bulwer Road
Other.Comments: Awful estate agents, DO NOT RENT A HOUSE WITH HABITIO!! House was a tip when we moved in, there was a lot of things broken which we'd made them aware of long before moving in yet they still did nothing to fix them, and throughout our tenancy they were terrible at dealing with any problems we had with the house, but despite all of this they hounded you for the rent and expected a spotless house when we moved out. Cannot emphasise enough DO NOT USE HABITIO.

Road.Name: 8 Tennyson Street
Other.Comments: Good house and responsive letting agents, if you're reasonable with them they'll be reasonable with you.

Road.Name: Tennyson Street
Other.Comments: Mould problems. Damp problems. Not sorted.

Road.Name: Adderley Road
Other.Comments:
Excellent property and excellent estate agents. 
Had a few issues throughout my two years at Adderley Road (Boiler breaking, back door not locking) and all were sorted out within 24 hours. They even managed to replace the entire boiler within this time frame!
Priya Properties seem to have a good relationship with the landlords that they deal with hence the quick problem resolution times.
Recommended!

Road.Name: Balfour Road
Other.Comments: Situated in the popular student region of Lenton this area is very close to the town centre and a short bus ride or 30 minute walk to the University's main campus. Relatively cheap rent combined with a fantastic landlord and excellent quality housing made my final year at University very enjoyable and problem free.

Road.Name: College Avenue East
National University of Singapore Office of Housing Services
Other.Comments: Located on the University Campus this student accommodation possesses state of the art study facilities as well as recreational activities such as an infinity pool and rock climbing wall. Rooms and apartments are fairly simple but reliable with Utown Residence possessing everything a student would need on a daily basis from several restaurants and food courts to a hairdressers. Options for air-conditioning are available with a "pay as you use" system which I would highly recommend due to the high temperatures and humidity levels in Singapore. Transport links to the rest of campus are very good from this accommodation but the nearest MRT station is slightly further than from the alternative Prince George Park Residence which makes getting into the city slightly more difficult. However, the facilities and social atmosphere on this part of campus make it the best choice when selecting accommodation.

Road.Name: Walham Yard
Other.Comments: If you're living in London, Marsh & Parsons were amazing. A lot of other people had so many landlord issues but for us everything was managed by the estate agency and they were super helpful.

Road.Name: Calais Hill
Other.Comments: Location is good because it's in city center, but bad as a result due to distance from uni.

Road.Name: Hyndland Road
Other.Comments: Beautiful flat, nice area but less lively for students (opposite way to unions, town, late night takeaways etc). Only reason we left was lack of living room/small kitchen but rooms were huge. Landlords good at fixing problems.

Road.Name: devana road
Other.Comments: Mice

Road.Name: Harefeild Road
Other.Comments: Good lamdlords, sorted problems quickly. For example ordered a new washing mechine strait away when the old one broke down. Landlords easy to get hold of too.

Road.Name: 1 Landseer Road
Other.Comments: Lovely house in a great location but the estate agents are a bit sow to respond to problems.

Road.Name: Filbert Street East
Other.Comments: Overcharging on deposit at the end of our tenancy. Very reluctant to solve problems with mould in 1 room and downright refused to solve mould problems in the other room, saying it was the tenants fault.

Road.Name: Prospect Street
Other.Comments:
Sam was friendly, easy to contact and always able to help with any problems that arose.
Even when I stupidly dismantled a wall socket and forgot how to put it back together again!
Would recommend the house and agency to anyone.

Road.Name: Horwood Close
Other.Comments: The condition we left our house in was much better than when we moved in, yet we were charged over £350 for cleaning (between 6) which came out of our deposits. The checkout report only mentioned dust on skirting boards and door frames but that was it. One tenant's room was so clean that the only thing the report mentioned was a couple of hairs in a drawer (which probably fell into it when they were cleaning it)! We got an independent cleaner to give us a quote before we started (£250) and then another independent cleaner quoted us £70 based on the checkout report we showed them (as we didn't have access to the house) so how College and County came to the figure of £350, we don't know! We were also charged for mattress protectors at £15 each - surely you would expect the landlord to replace these for hygiene reasons when there are new tenants or at least tell the new tenants to buy their own. We reported issues with an extractor fan and light in our shower room which was newly installed during our tenancy as well as broken sofas which were new for us. These issues certainly were not our fault in any way, so we weren't charged for them, but they still weren't sorted out before our tenancy ended. We were also charged for missing items that weren't there when our tenancy began - this included £20-£30 for each missing/broken fridge/freezer drawer (4 in total). Overall, we each received £455 out of the £540 that we each paid as a deposit. Most of the charges were ridiculous!
